frameDefinitions: This frame deals with testing or examination of someone's Knowledge or skill in a particular area.
This frame concerns an Evaluee being judged for its quality, i.e. how much it would probably be liked.
A Questioner asks a Witness (or defendant) questions in the context of a court procedure.
An Inspector directs his/her perceptual attention to a Ground to ascertain whether the Ground is intact or  whether an Unwanted_entity is present.
An organic item, the Patient, has undergone the natural process of rotting  and decaying with a possible expression of the Degree to which the rotting has occurred.
A Tester uses a concrete or conceptual Product in order to determine either whether it works or to find out how well or in which manner it works.
frameExamples: At the end of the trial period all three groups took an English for Commerce <t><fex name='Examination'>examination</fex></t> to assess progress.
We 'd like to <t>cross-examine</t> the witness if we can.
The police removed Flonnory and Barbour from the automobile and <t>frisked</t> them for weapons.
Sun has (hopefully) already <t>tested</t> it for compliance.
listRoleDefinitions: One who administers a test of some kind.
One who undergoes a test of some kind.
The ability, practice, or command of information on which an <fen>Examinee</fen> is tested.
A credential or status that one acquires by passing an <fen>Examination</fen>.
The <fen>Examination</fen> that somebody takes.
The time at which the examination occurs.
The location where the examination takes place.
The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged for its quality.
This role marks expressions that denote a scalar property of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> with respect to which the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is judged.
The individual who asks a <fen>Witness</fen> questions.
A person who is present in a courtroom in order to give some form of evidence, has been sworn in, and is being examined by a <fen>Questioner</fen>.
When the examination occurs.
Where the examination takes place.
The person who inspects the <fen>Ground</fen> to see if it is intact or without blemish.
The entity that the <fen>Inspector</fen> inspects with his senses to ascertain whether it is intact.
An entity whose presence would impair the acceptability or usefulness of the <fen>Ground</fen>.

Some of the words in this frame occur with a constituent that expresses the desired outcome of the inspection.  Normally this constituent is a PP Complement headed by <ment>for</ment>, or a <ment>to</ment>-marked VP Complement.
The desirable state of affairs which the <fen>Inspector</fen> hopes to find to obtain when inspecting the <fen>Ground</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Inspector</fen> examines the <fen>Ground</fen>.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the organic matter that has decayed.
The person who uses  the <fen>Product</fen> to see if it is intact or to ascertain its characteristics during operation.
The entity that the <fen>Tester</fen> uses  to ascertain whether it is intact.
An entity or property whose presence would impair the acceptability or usefulness of the <fen>Product</fen>.
An action that the <fen>Tester</fen> intends to accomplish subjecting the <fen>Product</fen> to a test of its functioning.
The desirable state of affairs which the <fen>Tester</fen> hopes to find to obtain when using the <fen>Product</fen>.
A variable of behavior of the <fen>Product</fen> which is specifically evaluated.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Tester</fen> uses  the <fen>Product</fen> to evaluate its functioning.
The location in which the test is carried out.
